Music Log Privacy Policy

Last updated: June 19th, 2023

This Privacy Policy describes how Music Log ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects the personal information of users ("you" or "your") when you use our mobile application, Music Log (the "App").

Information We Collect:
1.1 Personal Information: When you use the App, we may collect the following personal information from you:

Name
Email address
Age

1.2 Collection Method: We collect this personal information through user input within the App.

Use of Personal Information:
2.1 App Functionality: We use the collected personal information to provide you with access to the App's features and functionality.

2.2 Analytics: We may also use the personal information for analytical purposes to improve the App's performance and user experience.

Sharing of Personal Information:
3.1 Third-Party Disclosure: We do not share or disclose any of your personal information with third parties.

Storage and Security:
4.1 Data Storage: We store the collected personal information on secure servers, employing industry-standard security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.

Age Restrictions:
5.1 Age Requirements: The App does not have any age restrictions, and it is intended for use by individuals of all ages.

Cookies and Tracking:
6.1 Use of Cookies: The App does not use cookies or similar tracking technologies.

Advertisements:
7.1 Advertisements: The App does not display advertisements or utilize any third-party ad networks.

Data Deletion:
8.1 User Control: You have the right to delete any affiliated data stored within the App. Please refer to the App's settings or preferences to initiate the data deletion process.

Changes to this Privacy Policy:
9.1 Updates: We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be effective upon posting the revised policy on the App. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

Contact Us:
10.1 If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at [contact information].
